betterquesting.name: Finally Furnace
betterquesting.desc: Nothing glamorous, but this sturdy stone box will allow for simple processing of most ores.

betterquesting.name: Starting with Slag
betterquesting.desc: A waste of good iron ore, but it's a start.

betterquesting.name: Primitive Furnace
betterquesting.desc: The alchemic furnace provides access to some rather powerful early potions, as well as being an inefficient way to smelt iron dust. Needs water, fuel, and bottles.

betterquesting.name: Dry It
betterquesting.desc: Fluids left in the drying basin will evaporate over time, transforming into a solid item. This can be used to turn iron berry juice into iron dust.

betterquesting.name: Crush It
betterquesting.desc: Items placed in the crushing tub may be processed by jumping on them. This will produce a liquid and often an item byproduct. Sneak + Right Click will clear any fluid in the tub. Can be used to crush berries into juice, clay into bricks, and coal into dust.

betterquesting.name: Water Junk
betterquesting.desc: Many useful items can be strained out of these rivers, including valuable metal scraps. These strainers can be emptied by placing a hopper underneath.

betterquesting.name: Getting Wood
betterquesting.desc: You know how things start. Punch trees.

betterquesting.name: Hammer Time
betterquesting.desc: The right tools separate us from the nomads. With this we can begin to improve the inefficient processes relied upon by scavengers.

betterquesting.name: Light Machinery
betterquesting.desc: These blocks allow for the creation of machinery.

betterquesting.name: Adult Ore Processing
betterquesting.desc: Vodka seems to break down the metals within stone ores surprisingly well.

betterquesting.name: Tinker Table
betterquesting.desc: A more refined crafting table needed for some engineering components.

betterquesting.name: Calculated
betterquesting.desc: The kind of math they don't teach in school. Allows for adding together solid items. Needs to be charged before use.

betterquesting.name: Carpentry
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Multiblock Planning
betterquesting.desc: A picture of planned multiblocks can be found in the engineers manual. With this projector, those blueprints can be projected into the world.

betterquesting.name: Actually Casing
betterquesting.desc: This expensive casing can be used to craft more complex technology.

betterquesting.name: Hard Hat Required
betterquesting.desc: A heavier engineering block is needed for larger, more useful machines.

betterquesting.name: Smashing Table
betterquesting.desc: A sturdy steel table can be used to manually break down ores, increasing the overall yield when smelted.

betterquesting.name: Multiblock Furnace
betterquesting.desc: Turns iron and coke into steel.

betterquesting.name: Quest for Coke
betterquesting.desc: A more efficient form of coke and necessary step for early steel production.

betterquesting.name: Nether Already?
betterquesting.desc: The nether provides both dangerous monsters and useful crafting materials.

betterquesting.name: Gettin Tipsy
betterquesting.desc: The brewery can combine yeast and various plants into a rough grain alcohol. The distillery can refine this impure drink into a more useful solvent.

betterquesting.name: Cheap Frame
betterquesting.desc: Roughly thrown together. It's not pretty, but it works.

betterquesting.name: Better Processing
betterquesting.desc: A larger furnace that can be used to smelt two components together. Allows for early creation of various alloys and more efficient processing of some ores.

betterquesting.name: All Gold Case
betterquesting.desc: A very shiny case used to show other what nice things you have. Might also be used to craft more advanced machinery.

betterquesting.name: MFR.... sorta
betterquesting.desc: The basic building block of industrial forgoing. This allows for building more compact machinery.

betterquesting.name: Making Gas
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Turbines
betterquesting.desc: Materials needed to construct a 5x8x5 mekanism turbine

betterquesting.name: Gas Powered
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Bio Reactions
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Plant Oil
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Fluid Fuel
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Swamp Power
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Tree Powered
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: The Weird Ones
betterquesting.desc: Only 1 task needed to complete quest

betterquesting.name: The Weirdest Ones
betterquesting.desc: Only 1 of the 3 items needed to complete quest

betterquesting.name: Industrial for Farming
betterquesting.desc: The spore recreator produces mushrooms, perfect for a life sustained by mushroom stew.... or making yeast. The plant interactor gently harvests crops or fruits by collecting drops without breaking the plant.

betterquesting.name: Baby Thief
betterquesting.desc: A system for limiting the population! The baby separator is an active solution which moves baby animals to the back of the machine while the mob filter will passively let baby animals fall through.

betterquesting.name: Auto Babies
betterquesting.desc: Let's the animals do their thing while you're not around... or while you are around, whatever you're into. Should be combined with some system for limiting population.

betterquesting.name: Farming With Steve
betterquesting.desc: Note: cart assembler time requirement removed. Simply combine the cart parts and input coal to form Steve's farming cart.

betterquesting.name: Pro Chef Tools
betterquesting.desc: Enough tools you're going to need some place to put them all.

betterquesting.name: Quick Harvest
betterquesting.desc: Various options for speeding up crop growth exist. This small selection all function by being physically near the plants. Who says you're limited to just one type?

betterquesting.name: Expanding Seed Selection
betterquesting.desc: Breaks a large number of leaves or grass with a single strike. Effective for scavenging for seeds.

betterquesting.name: Cow Juice
betterquesting.desc: Milk: useful both for clearing poisons and as an ingredient in a wide variety of recipes.

betterquesting.name: Pro Kitchen
betterquesting.desc: A multiblock disguised as a simple kitchen pieces. Assembled by placing the various components next to one another.

betterquesting.name: High Tech Speed
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Farm Land Profits
betterquesting.desc: Pam will also buy almost any crop back from you. She pays particularly well for raw meats and mob drops.

betterquesting.name: Kitchen Staples
betterquesting.desc: Stocking your fridge with these staples will open up a great number of different recipes.

betterquesting.name: Giving a Shit
betterquesting.desc: Placed under animals, this will produce sewage. This waste can be refined into more useful items.

betterquesting.name: Let Them Come To You
betterquesting.desc: Needs to be filled with bait and surrounded by at least 5 grass blocks to generate drops.

betterquesting.name: Charged Metal
betterquesting.desc: (Only one task needed to complete quest) This rather strange metal seems to difficult to process without a great deal of power used to first excite the metal.

betterquesting.name: Pure Energy
betterquesting.desc: Harness lightning from the sky as a renewable source of power. Can also be used to directly charge some materials.

betterquesting.name: Magic Metal
betterquesting.desc: A mutated ingot of some kind, never even considered for mass production.

betterquesting.name: Spin Cycle
betterquesting.desc: A high tech centrifuge that can collect both the solid and liquid from processed items.

betterquesting.name: DNA Manipulator
betterquesting.desc: Mutagen, which proves useful for manipulating the DNA of bees, also seems to react in useful ways with other fluids.

betterquesting.name: Number Science
betterquesting.desc: Allows for dividing solid objects by other items, producing interesting and useful ingredients. Do not divide by diamond.

betterquesting.name: Atomic Numbers
betterquesting.desc: Harnessing the power of laser charged emeralds has allowed opened the way for adding 3 items together, providing expensive and powerful items.

betterquesting.name: Thermal Refined
betterquesting.desc: It's a machine frame.

betterquesting.name: In Need of Latex
betterquesting.desc: The tree fluid extractor must be placed with a log in front. The machine will extract fluid from the log, slowly breaking it. This latex should then be piped into the latex processing unit. The latex processing unit additionally needs water and RF to function.

betterquesting.name: Industrial Upgrade
betterquesting.desc: Unlocks many more machines for industrial foregoing.

betterquesting.name: Circuitry
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Laser Changer
betterquesting.desc: A high powered laser that proves effective at exciting some materials, converting them into a more crystallized form.

betterquesting.name: Expert MFR
betterquesting.desc: The base component for powerful machines that can duplicate mobs or generate ores.

betterquesting.name: Rock Extractor
betterquesting.desc: An automated system for extracting valuable materials from ore. Provides a better quality material compared to traditional smelting.

betterquesting.name: Empowering
betterquesting.desc: They glow. That's how you know they're expensive.

betterquesting.name: RF Infuser
betterquesting.desc: Well if one laser worked so well for creating new goods, naturally the next step is to shoot 4 high power lasers for extended durations to make even better things.

betterquesting.name: Lighting the Portal
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 of the 2 items needed to complete quest) With flint and steel out of reach, other methods of lighting the portal must be explored.

betterquesting.name: Extra Machines 2
betterquesting.desc: An combination of various metals provides a solid base for more... interesting machinery and power generation.

betterquesting.name: Big Steam Generator
betterquesting.desc: Enough block to make a 3x3 steam reactor

betterquesting.name: Super Steam Power
betterquesting.desc: Needed to make a small 5x4x5 turbine

betterquesting.name: Who Nerfs Chests?
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 item needed to complete quest.) Many different storage options exist as your collection of items grows.

betterquesting.name: A Bigger Storage Box
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest.) You could throw out some of those items you never use... or you could make a bigger box to store them in.

betterquesting.name: Electronic Storage
betterquesting.desc: (Only one task needs to be completed for the quest) An electronic storage system allows for a great deal of items to be contained in a single location, though these systems require power to be accessed.

betterquesting.name: Deep Ore Injections
betterquesting.desc: It seems that bee DNA contains a fantastic enzyme for breaking down difficult to process metals. Refined aerotheum seems to break down these ores even more cleanly. The injection tool can either be crafted with the ore or used by right clicking in world.

betterquesting.name: Hard to Process
betterquesting.desc: To hard to process by traditional methods, tungsten must first be broken down by more extreme solvents.

betterquesting.name: RF Base
betterquesting.desc: The core component to RFTool's devices. A basic building block for the mod's apparatus. A frame to their machines, if you will.

betterquesting.name: Multi System Storage
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest) With great strides in technology comes the ability to connect multiple storage systems into one easy to use location.

betterquesting.name: Bloody Crafting
betterquesting.desc: Retains the blood of living creature slain while in the users inventory.

betterquesting.name: Programming Magic
betterquesting.desc: The CAD assembler can combine the various CAD parts into a fully functioning magic gun.

betterquesting.name: Psionic Metal
betterquesting.desc: A creation of directly infusing psi energy into gold ingots through the infusion trick.

betterquesting.name: Space Wand
betterquesting.desc: A wand specially attuned to specific crystals found deep underground. When held at night, the wand will mark the location of rock crystal.

betterquesting.name: A Place for Petals
betterquesting.desc: Can form magical flowers by combining mystical petals found in the wild.

betterquesting.name: Space Metal
betterquesting.desc: Not receptive to the low heat of traditional furnaces, the rock containing starmetal seems to easily melt away by the evil within the blood infusion process.

betterquesting.name: Bigger Drum Set
betterquesting.desc: A high density starlight table with more room for crafting. Unlock accesses to many useful tools such as craftable floating crystals.

betterquesting.name: Evil Sticks
betterquesting.desc: Not only a useful ingredient in broom making, these sticks are attuned to evil shrines and will point to the nearest one when dropped on the ground. However, cities have been known to tear down these evil structures and pave over them.

betterquesting.name: Soul Shredder
betterquesting.desc: Not content with just trapping spirits, this ring shreds the everlasting soul of lingering spirits. The essence dropped by these spirits my be useful in some advanced items.

betterquesting.name: Runecraft
betterquesting.desc: By translating mana energy into runes crafted onto living wood, these items can then be used to craft greater magical items.

betterquesting.name: Blood Furnace
betterquesting.desc: A modified furnace capable of manipulating blood without the risk of it hardening.

betterquesting.name: Seeing Ghosts
betterquesting.desc: Combining the celestial crystal with a bit of evil provides a way to see into a dimension thats been hiding in plain sight. Shift right clicking with the ring will provide buffs and allow the player to see spirits. However, the spirits will take notice of this power.

betterquesting.name: Storage Anywhere
betterquesting.desc: (Only one task needed to complete quest) A high tech storage solution can be even more useful when accessible from a distance.

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #7
betterquesting.desc: Eureka!  Not only are materials science and electricity different in this world… math itself seems to have strange, material altering properties!  I do not know if I am starting to understand the physics of this universe or have finally gone mad.  I mock my friends for dabbling with blood and starlight but when 2+2=gold… am I any different? I should tell her, next time I visit.  As soon as I trim my beard… and bathe… and perhaps I should bring her something… hmmmm.

betterquesting.name: Farming the River
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete the quest.) An improved net could pull even more useful junk from these rivers.

betterquesting.name: Finding the best spot
betterquesting.desc: Collecting junk is more efficient in flowing water, oceans, and rivers. This tool lets you check the efficiency of your setup.

betterquesting.name: Better than Potions
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest.) Unlike potions, elixirs can be placed into stacks of 16, allowing for multiple to be carried without wasting valuable inventory space.

betterquesting.name: Super Brewer
betterquesting.desc: Stronger elixirs require an alchemic furnace built from stronger bricks found in the nether.

betterquesting.name: Liquid Armor
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest.) Advanced elixirs can provide significant boosts. Regeneration, fire protection, and bonus natural armor can be brewed with the right natural ingredients.

betterquesting.name: Wine Fortified
betterquesting.desc: Iron berry juice, while quite poisonous when drunk, can be fermented into iron wine. This brew allows the drinker to last longer in battle.

betterquesting.name: T2 Hidden
betterquesting.desc: Only used for locking other quests behind T2

betterquesting.name: RF Furnace
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest.) With sufficient power, burning coal seems primitive.

betterquesting.name: Base Defender
betterquesting.desc: Sure you can live in a bunker like some sort of hobbit. But the idea of mowing down zombies with a high power turret holds a certain appeal.

betterquesting.name: Handheld Rock Smasher
betterquesting.desc: While biodiesel can be useful for large scale power production, it also allows for a portable gas power drill which remove much more stone than your standard pick axe. Upgrade to the drill can be applied in the engineers workbench.

betterquesting.name: Oil from Plants
betterquesting.desc: The squeezer uses great pressure to extract the oil from seed. This high pressure may be useful for other processes.

betterquesting.name: Refinement
betterquesting.desc: Refining plant oil and ethanol produces biodiesel, an extremely energy dense fuel.

betterquesting.name: Fermenter
betterquesting.desc: The fermenter can be used to convert plant matter into ethanol, a necessary ingredient for biodiesel.

betterquesting.name: Measured Flow
betterquesting.desc: And early system for judging the flow of power can be useful to determine the overall usage or production of various power systems.

betterquesting.name: Power to Go
betterquesting.desc: Sometimes you just need to strap a battery to your back.

betterquesting.name: Sniper Steve
betterquesting.desc: The railgun uses power to launch iron or steel rods great distances, dealing significant damage. This process does require a bit of charge up before shooting.

betterquesting.name: Serious Farmer
betterquesting.desc: A watering can with built in WiFi-Water technology. Allows for users to indiscriminately spray everything with water.

betterquesting.name: Super Worm
betterquesting.desc: Lasts for an unlimited duration in the fishing water strainer. Plus it glows.

betterquesting.name: Well Read
betterquesting.desc: Automatically fills with random books when place. Perfect for the hoarder who loves to collect books they'll never read.

betterquesting.name: Unlimited Grid
betterquesting.desc: Warning: Cannot be moved once placed. Allows for users to completely forget the GP system exists.

betterquesting.name: Black Hole Box
betterquesting.desc: Allows for drawers to hold a near infinite number of items.

betterquesting.name: Blood Bank
betterquesting.desc: An infinite source of blood. No specific blood really, we just mix them all together.

betterquesting.name: High Power
betterquesting.desc: Based on the technology of draconic reactors, this tiny box outputs an impressive amount of energy.

betterquesting.name: Full Tank
betterquesting.desc: Thanks to breakthroughs in the science of quantum homeopathy and water memory, this tank will provide an unlimited amount of any fluid provided to it. Although, this does make it more difficult to empty.

betterquesting.name: Full of Hot Air
betterquesting.desc: Not actually unlimited gas, it just mixes the given gas with air and outputs a more diluted product. None seems to notice though. Prefers to be filled within a machine or tank gui but happily outputs to gas tubes.

betterquesting.name: Vazkii's Tears
betterquesting.desc: Based on ancient daybloom technology, provides a bottom less source of mana.

betterquesting.name: T3 Hidden
betterquesting.desc: Only used for locking other quests behind T3

betterquesting.name: Mob Juicifier
betterquesting.desc: "Processes" mobs into their base components, pink slime and liquid meat.

betterquesting.name: Dragons Core
betterquesting.desc: The basic component for draconic tools and machines.

betterquesting.name: Wyvern Upgrade
betterquesting.desc: The basic draconic core upgraded with spirit essence and otherworldly metals.

betterquesting.name: Woke Core
betterquesting.desc: With high amounts of power and some additional catalysts, the daconium can become awakened.

betterquesting.name: Chaos
betterquesting.desc: Crafted from cores guarded by near immortal dragons. A highly prized item containing great power.

betterquesting.name: Heart of Stone
betterquesting.desc: A dragon heart encased in solid stone. Perfect for pressing into molds to mass produce more hearts.

betterquesting.name: Mek Box
betterquesting.desc: A simple frame crafted from difficult to acquire parts. The base of mekanism machines.

betterquesting.name: Expensive Mek Box
betterquesting.desc: Infused with liquid obsidian, theses cases are even more sturdy than the original design. Requires 10 refined obsidian ingots to complete the strengthening process.

betterquesting.name: Frame of Experience
betterquesting.desc: Unlocks many blocks for processing materials with TE.

betterquesting.name: Creator of Worlds
betterquesting.desc: Used to inscribe new worlds onto metal tablets. Useful for creating large worlds with difficult to find materials or ores not found in the overworld.

betterquesting.name: Foreign Metals
betterquesting.desc: Spoiler: Not found in the overworld.

betterquesting.name: Ender Infused
betterquesting.desc: An ingot made from a mixture of part magic and part technology, perfect for crafting machines so complex they border on the verge of sorcery.

betterquesting.name: Super Hot
betterquesting.desc: The pinnacle of furnace technology, capable of smelting multiple ingots from a single ore. Also needed to produce the exceptionally high temperatures required to smelt advanced alloys.

betterquesting.name: A Bigger Table
betterquesting.desc: A bigger table to make better items.

betterquesting.name: Excessive Crafting
betterquesting.desc: A massive table for creating items that break the traditional rules of the universe.

betterquesting.name: It Takes Effort
betterquesting.desc: The highest tier of crafting table... that is until we perfect the 9x9x9 3D crafting table.

betterquesting.name: Blue Gold
betterquesting.desc: Yellorium may be stabilized by being injected with a very cool liquid. This stabilized fuel makes for the perfect building material for sensitive electronics capable of auto-crafting nearly any object.

betterquesting.name: Craft on Demand
betterquesting.desc: The base unit for the CPU multiblock needed for AE auto-crafting.

betterquesting.name: Mini Mint
betterquesting.desc: Presses ingots into small disks imprinted with a signature design. Makes the metal seem more expensive. Can be used to turn excess metal into a bit of power.

betterquesting.name: Dragon Essence
betterquesting.desc: A synthetic substitute for dragons blood, which can be molded into a heart.

betterquesting.name: Dragon Empowered
betterquesting.desc: Unable to be simply crafted together, draconic gear requires materials be infused at high power.

betterquesting.name: Furnace Hidden
betterquesting.desc: Used in case players skip progression by finding a furnace

betterquesting.name: XRAY Glasses
betterquesting.desc: Using laser irradiated lapis has the strange benefit of detecting entities through solid walls. Totally safe to put directly next to your eyes... probably.

betterquesting.name: Teleportation Wand
betterquesting.desc: When walking seems mundane, harness the power of endermen to teleport in the blink of an eye. With some refinement, this power could be focused to exact location rather than random hopping.

betterquesting.name: A Fancier Torch
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needs to be completed for quest) A high tech tinkerer deserves better than burning sticks to light their workspace.

betterquesting.name: Staying Stocked
betterquesting.desc: Not limited to just accessing boxes of items, the player interface allows for automated extraction or insertion of items directly into your hands, even when far from home. Both reinforced retrieval nodes and transfer filters can be used to limit items to a specific number in inventory.

betterquesting.name: A Second /home
betterquesting.desc: (Only 1 task needed to complete quest) Allows for quick travel between distant locations.

betterquesting.name: Trashman #1
betterquesting.desc: Trash and bones, trash and bones, how long until I am trash and bones as well?  We have all come to this horrid place and that is all we leave behind, to be found by the next fools stranded here with no hope of escape.  Well, I am the Trashpicker and I leave you this as my bones: this motley collection of journals and tips, attempts and failures I have collected in my wanderings through this world.  May it do you more good than it did me.

betterquesting.name: Trashman #2
betterquesting.desc: So many civilizations have built and collapsed in this cursed world that the very water is full of their trash.  Build yourself a strainer and you too can become a trashpicker, building on the failures of the past! Be sure you drink the water upriver of these stinking cities, now that you have seen what is in these rivers.

You've awaken from slumber once more, but the world seems different.  Empty.  You do not know where you came from or how you got here, to this land of ancient ruins and deserted cities.  You see no clear goal but survival and the echoing ruins imply that this might not be an easy task.  Your only clue as to how this place came to be is a faded, cobbled together journal left in a sturdy chest near the clearing where you awoke, marked with a tattered flag that was once red and is now as faded as the rest of this land.

betterquesting.name: Trashman #3
betterquesting.desc: Besides the river flotsam that clogs your nets, you'll find bits of scrap to open and sort, hoping for something that will put you past scraping in the muck.  Better trash can be found in the city dumps... if you can stomach the smell as you dig.

betterquesting.name: The Craftsman #2
betterquesting.desc: I think these people built too quickly and not well.  All their work has come to ruin and I avoid it as I walk the wilderness in search of food and forage.  I shall not fall into their ways but make each item with care.  I have been experimenting with improvements on even the simple chest, sketching out variations to try.

betterquesting.name: The Craftsman #1
betterquesting.desc: I know not how I came to be here, but little purpose is served by idle thoughts and so I shall set to work.  The cities seem unwholesome places, reeking of trash and decay.  I shall start afresh, with the clean scent of wind and sawdust, and build a home for myself.

betterquesting.name: The Craftsman #3
betterquesting.desc: There is peace to be found in working with your hands.  I try to fall into this peace each day, try to resist the desire to go searching, to look for life, for any other living soul... but that way leads to madness.  I shall stay here and improve my designs, finding comfort in my work.

betterquesting.name: The Craftsman #4
betterquesting.desc: No more will I scavenge at the edge of cities, for even the bits of metal I need for hinges and locks, nature has provided! The berries I collect from the peculiar trees, or dredge out of the river waters, can be crushed and refined.  I must take this as a sign to wander no more to those accursed places.

betterquesting.name: Craftsman #5
betterquesting.desc: I am so lonely… I stroke my fine wood but it brings me no comfort, and my tools do not speak back.  The wind calls to me but I dare not reply for I will not then know if the world has gone mad or only me.  I huddle here amongst the fine things I have made, but now I am interested only in making more ale for it is the only comfort left to me.

betterquesting.name: The Main Line
betterquesting.desc: Welcome to the world of Undiscovered. This book aims to be your guide into this new world. Main quests are noted by a decorative shape and directly contribute to the advancement of technology or magic.

betterquesting.name: A Side Track
betterquesting.desc:
Side quests are marked by a plain square outline. These quest may highlight items that can provide useful, but not strictly necessary, to your journey.
     Lore quests are marked with the book and quill icon, like the quest above this one. These quest merely provide a background to this world, but their words fill you with determination.

betterquesting.name: A More Sturdy Pick
betterquesting.desc: The commonly used diamond pick seems rather flimsy, perhaps the diamonds can be used to reinforce a picks made with a quality gem core.

betterquesting.name: Getting Closure
betterquesting.desc: With a modified version of the ring, you are able to push spirits with a strong beam. Perhaps pushing them into a box designed to contain spirits could have future uses.

betterquesting.name: Runic Power
betterquesting.desc: The basic rune types. These are not consumed if used in other runic altar recipes.

betterquesting.name: Soul Food
betterquesting.desc: The spirit furnace is able to recreate living beings from the trapped souls using some blood. This allows for farming of items dropped by these creatures.

betterquesting.name: Space Ores
betterquesting.desc: Iron ore seems to react strangely to focused starlight. The metal itself changes when light from an astral crystal is linked to the ore.

betterquesting.name: Exotic Shards
betterquesting.desc: Found in RFTools dimensions. Can be used to infuse machines making them more efficient.

betterquesting.name: Magic Pistol
betterquesting.desc: The most basic CAD requires only the iron assembly, which contains enough power to create psi dust.

betterquesting.name: Purifier
betterquesting.desc: Changes the properties of blocks placed near the flower.

betterquesting.name: Angel Dust
betterquesting.desc: Created by shooting redstone with the basic iron CAD.

betterquesting.name: Blood Diamond
betterquesting.desc: Needed for more advanced blood manipulation, the dark gem is created by throwing a dark gem into a pool of at least 5 blocks of fluid blood. But be quick as the blood will harden if left to sit.

betterquesting.name: Living Wood
betterquesting.desc: Magically attuned wood, more receptive to the mana flowing within the mystic flowers.

betterquesting.name: Pure Rocks
betterquesting.desc: By purifying the hellish nature of netherack, a more refined rock is created.

betterquesting.name: Flower Conductor
betterquesting.desc: Strapping a few pretty leaves to some magical wood seems to be enough to interact with these mystical flowers.

betterquesting.name: Unholy Wood
betterquesting.desc: Tainted by the blood collected from the living, this sapling has unholy properties not found in natural wood.

betterquesting.name: Pinky Promise
betterquesting.desc: Condensed gold and astral magic allow for unnatural amounts of blood to be stored within the infuser.

betterquesting.name: Promises, Promises
betterquesting.desc: An augment used to increase the capacity and power of the blood infuser.

betterquesting.name: Sky Infused Crystal
betterquesting.desc: An improvement over raw rock crystals, the celestial crystal is grown from celestial crystal clusters, which are formed when a rock crystal and starmetal dust soak in liquid starlight.

betterquesting.name: Mana Bowl
betterquesting.desc: A container that hold the natural mana essence of flowers.

betterquesting.name: Holy Wood
betterquesting.desc: The once tainted logs of the undead can be purified again, which seem to glow from the life essence now purified.

betterquesting.name: Golden Gun
betterquesting.desc: A more advanced assembly capable of casting spells of greater complexity.

betterquesting.name: Potential Realized
betterquesting.desc: Created by charging the inverted potentia with lightning. Can be created by direct lightning strikes or by using the environmental accumulator during a thunder storm. The sceptre of thunder or the psi smite trick could be useful here.

betterquesting.name: Biome in a Bottle
betterquesting.desc: These biome bottle can modify the current biome of an area. They may also be useful in crafting portal to unknown worlds.

betterquesting.name: Psi Diamonds
betterquesting.desc: Diamonds infused directly with the greater infusion trick.

betterquesting.name: What's Your Sign?
betterquesting.desc: Unlocks the ability to attune both crystals and yourself to specific constellations. This attunement unlocks some of the more powerful aspects of astral magic.

betterquesting.name: Diamond Vows
betterquesting.desc: The highest level of promise. Til undeath do you part.

betterquesting.name: Portable Accumulation
betterquesting.desc: When you can't find an environmental accumulator in just the right spot, a portable version of this infuser is needed. Requires 8 dark tanks filled with a significant amount of blood placed in specific locations around the accumulator to work.

betterquesting.name: Deep Earth Crystals
betterquesting.desc: Found very rarely near bedrock.

betterquesting.name: Flower Power
betterquesting.desc:
(Only one task needed to complete quest) 
With simple coal eating flower more difficult to create, botanists must consider some of the more unusual mystical flowers. 

Rafflowsia - Consumes other mana generating flowers for power 
Thermalily - Consumes lava sources for power with a long cool down 
Spectrolus - Consumes colored wool in a specific order for mana 
Hydroangeas - Consumes water source blocks for mana (has a limited life span)

betterquesting.name: Mage's Glock
betterquesting.desc: A very powerful CAD capable of accepting even more complex spells.

betterquesting.name: Star Fluid
betterquesting.desc: This crucible can collect starlight in its melted form. Not only useful in the crafting of more advance astral gadgets, this liquid illuminates its surroundings and provides night vision to those who touch it.

betterquesting.name: Crafting by Starlight
betterquesting.desc: A more refined crafting table, capable of absorbing greater quantities of starlight.

betterquesting.name: Custom Dimlets
betterquesting.desc: Used to create custom dimlets out of parts obtained from dimlet packages or through deconstructing other dimlets.

betterquesting.name: Star Soaked
betterquesting.desc: Creating an altar designed to radiate starlight on a single point allows for the refinement, enhancement, and even improvement of items placed in the center. Requires 12 buckets of liquid starlight to function, which have a chance to be consumed in crafting.

betterquesting.name: EDM Gem
betterquesting.desc: While somewhat unfocused energy, these resonating crystals seem to be key ingredients it more sophisticated magic.

betterquesting.name: Elf Dimension
betterquesting.desc: The material required to construct a portal between our world and alfheim. Also needs a significant source of mana to initially open the gate.

betterquesting.name: Space Assimilation
betterquesting.desc: Crystals can be attuned in a similar manner to living beings. This passes the strength of the attuned constellation onto the crystal.

betterquesting.name: Night Light
betterquesting.desc: A hand crafted version of the naturally occurring crystals. Provides starlight to any block or crafting table it is linked to.

betterquesting.name: Extreme Star Craft
betterquesting.desc: The final tier of starlight crafting, only for the most dedicated of Astral mages. Unlocks access to powerful equipment, including robes rumored to defend against draconic threats.

betterquesting.name: Additional Construction
betterquesting.desc: Modified pylons that seem to be in tunes with the Guardian of the Gaia. A beacon surrounded by 4 gaia pylons are required to summon the guardian.

betterquesting.name: Elvish Steel
betterquesting.desc: An advanced magical alloy capable of connecting to the elves who invented it. May also call down a stronger opponent, given a proper arena.

betterquesting.name: Soul Shards
betterquesting.desc: A trophy from killing the Guardian of the Gaia. Has a powerful concentration of magic pulsing within.

betterquesting.name: Agglomerated
betterquesting.desc: With a large concentration of mana, the agglomeration plate can combine the mana pearl, mana diamond, and mana steel into a stronger, greener ingot.

betterquesting.name: Mana Switcheroo
betterquesting.desc: Allows for the duplication of item though the use of mana. Also allows for a more easily automated form of psi materials.

betterquesting.name: Mage Programming
betterquesting.desc: Allows for the creation of more complex spells that can be stored in bullets.

betterquesting.name: Book of Darkness
betterquesting.desc: The guide to all things evil can be created by feeding the dark apple to a pig and throwing a book at the resulting dark orb.

betterquesting.name: Expanding Supply
betterquesting.desc: The capacity of the blood extractor can be increased by combining the blood extractor with a dark tank or another blood extractor. A Dark Tank's capacity can also be expanded in a similar way. By combining two tanks together, the capacity of both tanks will be combined.

betterquesting.name: Superior Stargazing
betterquesting.desc: While starlight is more potent higher in the sky, some locations in the world are naturally more receptive to starlight. While holding this device, strong sources of starlight will appear as dark starry clouds on the ground.

betterquesting.name: Ebony & Ivory
betterquesting.desc: The final tier of psi materials. Created by using the greater infusion trick on either coal or nether quartz while in the End.

betterquesting.name: Powering the Planet
betterquesting.desc: Once built, the dimensions must be powered. Be sure to have the dimension builder chunk loaded to prevent the world running out of power while inside.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #2
betterquesting.desc: This is the magic of my father: a magic of blood and earth and viscera, born of rage and fear.  A magic of chaos.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #1
betterquesting.desc: This is the magic of my mother: a magic of reaching out while staying safe, a magic of straight lines and clean math.  A magic of control.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #3
betterquesting.desc: My mother says it is no surprise that my father's magic starts with crystal and syringes, shaking her head.  Yet another bit of their past that I don't understand.  As a child, I begged for stories and she rarely let anything slip.  When she got older… well, by then I knew that this world was my world and had little interest in theirs.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #5
betterquesting.desc: After putting me to bed, my mother would often climb her tower and stare up at the stars.  At first I'm sure she was searching for something familiar, a way home.  But she soon found they had a power and beauty all their own… and learned how to harness it.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #6
betterquesting.desc: Apparently even my father can tire of blood eventually, because on one of his rare visits, Tinker helped him rig up a few things.  The Sanguinary Pedestal saves you a lot of time on laundry by automating blood collection and the blood infuser gives you more time to work with that fresh blood and a lot less waste.  The two men have never been friends, but Tinker can never resist working a problem.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #11
betterquesting.desc: My mother was very frustrated when she first tried to get her newest discovery, starmetal, to successfully smelt.  Tinker tried to help her but they couldn't get the heat to sustain at a high enough level; he was muttering about arc power and signalum upgrades as he wandered off.  It was my father who finally solved it, much to her chagrin. Say what you will about him, he would always come when she needed him, even if he couldn't figure out how to stay.  She called him horrid names at times… but also called him her “last man on earth” and always welcomed him back.

betterquesting.name: Pedestal of Blood
betterquesting.desc: Used to automate the collection of blood. Particularly useful when spikes are affixed to the top to drain the blood of creatures walking over the pedestal.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #7
betterquesting.desc: Not everything my father touches was death and blood.  All that cleanup led him to develop some very clever plumbing that rivals anything the fools in the lost cities had… I mean, did those people never have to use a toilet?  My father's inventions made cleanup a breeze and are useful for any number of things!

betterquesting.name: Evil H2O
betterquesting.desc: A bucket with an endless supply of water, yet always has room to accept more.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #8
betterquesting.desc: I was 15 when I made my own first magic.  After yet another fight with my mother, I fled to the woods, picking the flowers there that shimmered slightly in the coming twilight.  In this world, nearly everything seems to have more uses than meet the eye but it took me two months of experimentation before I had my first functional apothecary and created a Pure Daisy, so called because of the daze my life had been before discovering the powerful flowers.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #9
betterquesting.desc: I do not think I have ever been angrier than when my father took one of my own very first magical innovations -- the wood suffused with the botanical magic of this world -- and put it into his blood infuser to make something abominable.  I immediately cut down those cursed trees and tried to purify them again before they could infect the rest of the forest.  The logs transformed into something with properties all its own, which seemed attuned to the star magic my mother had started investigating in her later years.

betterquesting.name: King of the Nether
betterquesting.desc: Got milk?

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #1
betterquesting.desc: This world is strange in more ways than just the obvious.  The very rules of science seem to be different; currents and metals work in different ways.  It is clear that they were once very sophisticated; their skyscrapers are built of mysterious and wondrous materials and you find remains of their gears and circuits everywhere.  I refuse to give up and live like a caveman or follow the path of magic and madness like my friends.  I will pick away at this problem until I understand!

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #2
betterquesting.desc: I seem to be missing some very basic materials.  I see them in the buildings and in the detritus but they are completely absent from my core samples.  Finally I found a tower with an odd doorway.  After months of trying, it was finally my friend who gave me the materials to light an eerie fire and open the door to… I do not know how to describe it.  It scares me and fills me with hope, for here are the missing pieces!

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #3
betterquesting.desc: I found a crazy assortment of brewing apparatus and stills (and a lot of broken bottles) in an abandoned cottage up the hills.  I think the hermit is long dead, but I've been tinkering with his equipment and I think I might be able to improve on his designs and put it to a more industrial use. If this doesn't work to improve my ore processing, I may take up drinking myself.

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #4
betterquesting.desc: Now that I seem to have the basic materials, I need to go about this a little more methodically. Enough custom gears and individual design.  I think I can make some basic components that I can assemble and customize to different needs.

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #5
betterquesting.desc: For my smaller machines, I think if I build them into a standard casing it will allow me to rearrange my systems easily.  And one style of case should work for everything, right? Right!?  Right….

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #6
betterquesting.desc: The bees seem to be bothered by the chemical smells of my workshop… perhaps if I make a more natural appearing (and smelling) piece of machinery to process their output and supplies, they won't sting me so much.  Please.  Effing bees…

betterquesting.name: Tinker's Notebook #8
betterquesting.desc: I have created some more prototypes of machine casings.  After extensive testing, it is my plan to consolidate them all into one consistent, easy-to-manufacture style.  I am totally putting that on my to-do list… as soon as i find it.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #11
betterquesting.desc: Having brought the magic of my mother and the magic of my father into some sort of uneasy cooperation, I was able to bring my own magic to the next level.  The way my mother's magic let you pre-program an event, when combined with the visceral worldliness that my father preferred let me capture those natural forces into a token that I could reuse and re-purpose at need.  I called it the Runic Altar in honor of this combination of Symbol and Sanguine.

betterquesting.name: The Only Child #4
betterquesting.desc: Once my mother had planned out an action for her magic to do, she had to put it into a form that was more portable to interact with the world.  Although she was not a violent woman, it amused her that her tool was in the shape of a gun, since it was used to "execute" a command.  One of the first things she created was a more malleable form of the redstone dust that Tinker used to control his mechanicals.

betterquesting.name: Burning Gas
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: T3 Power
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: True Power
betterquesting.desc: No Description

betterquesting.name: Fluid Mover
betterquesting.desc: Using the broken plates salvaged from junk bags in the river, you can make a simple bucket.

betterquesting.name: Found a Bucket Hidden
betterquesting.desc: Used in case players skip progression by finding a bucket

betterquesting.name: More from Ore
betterquesting.desc: Placing the rocky ores in a sluice box then washing them with a bucket of water can uncover extra metal dusts hiding in the ore. This process cannot be automated and the dusts obtained cannot be used to craft other items.

betterquesting.name: Burning the Junk
betterquesting.desc: With so many sticks clogging up the strainers, it might be helpful to combine them into bundles for easy fuel.

betterquesting.name: Selection of Seeds
betterquesting.desc: A small sample of a number of useful seeds. Plants like fluffy puff can be crafting into various items, flax produces string, and hemp can be used for upgraded wires and nets.

betterquesting.name: Buying What You Can't Grow
betterquesting.desc: Pam's market sells a wide variety of seeds, saplings, and spawn eggs. Garlic coins can be found in chests or crafted (consider buying garlic seeds with your first garlic coin).

betterquesting.name: Kitchenaid
betterquesting.desc: 4 bricks and a stick to make a cooking pot? Sure why not.

betterquesting.name: Eat to Grow
betterquesting.desc: Spice of Life - Carrot Edition (aka the spice of life you won't hate). By eating a number of different foods, you can increase your max health. Gain your first additional heart by consuming 25 different foods. Gain a maximum of 10 additional hearts at 240 different foods consumed. Food tooltips will show if they have been previously eaten.

betterquesting.name: Food Squisher
betterquesting.desc: Once known as a squisher of soybeans, the food press can not squeeze fruits into juice, wood into logs, and water into bubbly water.

betterquesting.name: Food of the Gods
betterquesting.desc: Top tier foods can be eaten regardless of hunger level and will provide players with strength and resistance buffs.

betterquesting.name: Full Auto Farming
betterquesting.desc: Not all farmers are created equal, but all will harvest crops while you're busy slaying dragons.

betterquesting.name: Natural Resources
betterquesting.desc: Just like mining ores, except it's live animals.

betterquesting.name: Cow Disassembly Plant
betterquesting.desc: Great for turning cute creatures into crafting components. (If you're on a server, be nice and hook some lights to an online detector to automatically turn off mob farms while you're away)

betterquesting.name: People Farm
betterquesting.desc: Allows for trading with an imprisoned villager with 100 percent less moaning. Can also be automated.

betterquesting.name: One Fruit, Many Foods
betterquesting.desc: With a few different cooking tools and some simple kitchen staples, a single fruit can be processed into a number of different food items.

betterquesting.name: Not the Bees
betterquesting.desc: Rustic bees can be found hanging from trees. Pam's bees only appear in chests or their larva can be purchased from the market. Both function by simply placing the bee inside the apiary

betterquesting.name: Miss Martha's Guidebook #1
betterquesting.desc:
Miss Martha's Guidebook for Survival on a Hostile Planet (without getting your white pants dirty) - Animals 
 
Animals smell Bad.  The sooner you can Not Touch Them Ever, the better.  One simple method is to make a special jar, trap a cow on top of it and then drop an anvil on its nasty head.  So much cleaner now! More heavily automated options are even better because you can lock the filthy animals underground and never let them see the light of day ever again.  Fabulous!

betterquesting.name: Miss Martha's Guidebook #2
betterquesting.desc:
Miss Martha's Guidebook for Survival on a Hostile Planet (without getting your white pants dirty) - Bees 
 
The health and beauty benefits of honey are well known, so I don't have to tell you that!  But there are so many options it can be bewildering for the discerning consumer.  Today we are going to do a quick review and comparison of the options available on this godforsaken wasteland.  The simple Rustic bees are clearly native; they have very high production and boost the growth of nearby plants.  The more elusive Pam's honey bees produce much slower, but are great for food and candles… and I'm sure this royal jelly will have cosmetic properties.  Then there are the diverse and mysterious (and painful) bees that seem to vary by biome.  Slow and troublesome, they do show promise in the long run.

betterquesting.name: Miss Martha's Guidebook #3
betterquesting.desc:
Miss Martha's Guidebook for Survival on a Hostile Planet (without getting your white pants dirty) - Cooking 
 
The newest and fastest growing trend in cooking is… old and slow! Slowly braising wild caught ingredients in clay crockery, frying an egg on a heated ceramic disc by a wood fire, adding a touch of smoke and depth.  A rustic, hand-pressed juice… 

Who are we kidding. I just beat two rocks together and licked up what squirts out .  I hate my life.

betterquesting.name: Miss Martha's Guidebook #4
betterquesting.desc:
Miss Martha's Guidebook for Survival on a Hostile Planet (without getting your white pants dirty) - Kitchen 
 
When laying out a kitchen, it is important that not only is the space functional and well organized, but also well lit and decorated! A well placed window for natural light and some attractive framed art of a dead chicken or other hunting trophy add color and flair.  If nothing else is available, perhaps a potato print… of the poisonous variety.

betterquesting.name: Miss Martha's Guidebook #5
betterquesting.desc:
Miss Martha's Guidebook for Survival on a Hostile Planet (without getting your white pants dirty) - Balanced Diet 
 
Have you been eating too much steak and baked potatoes?  Is your waistline growing, along with your bathroom time? Time to vary that diet, get some fiber, and stay Heart Smart! For every 25 unique foods you eat, your heart will grow a little stronger and beat a little harder, letting you fight, mine, or love for just a little bit longer each day.  So get off that fat ass and start varying your diet.

betterquesting.name: Resonating Transformation
betterquesting.desc: Vibrates so fast things turn into other things.

betterquesting.name: Transforming Stone
betterquesting.desc: Stone placed near the marimorphosis will transform into a random biome variation. The stone is 12 times more likely to transform into the biome variant matching the biome where it is placed.

betterquesting.name: Into the Depths
betterquesting.desc: Standing on the deep dark portal will teleport you into a dimension which contains a great number of ores... and monsters. Be sure to bring light, as the dark will hurt you.

betterquesting.name: City Block
betterquesting.desc:
The lost city dimension is almost entirely filled with cities without damage. Great for looting or finding ores that don't generate in the overworld. Created by placing a bed on top of 2 empowered restonia blocks and surrounding the bed with 6 skulls. 
   Be sure to bring the materials to create a second portal with you, or another method of returning home.

betterquesting.name: A Superior Cobble Gen
betterquesting.desc: Not only capable of generating cobble, this machine can be configured to crush, smelt, or craft. Useful for producing smooth stone, polished stone, stone bricks, gravel, sand, glass, and even silicon.

betterquesting.name: Meaty Supply
betterquesting.desc: By injecting liquid meat right into your veins, you'll never go hungry again. Will auto supply liquid meat while in your inventory.

betterquesting.name: Spontaneous Reformation
betterquesting.desc: Dropped from pink slimes. These mobs naturally spawn in pools of liquid pink slime.

betterquesting.name: Getting It In and Out
betterquesting.desc:
The cart manager, when placed next to a detector rail, can be used to automatically input or extract item from the cart. Clicking the center button will allow each side to have a separate behavior. This can be used to configure a single cargo manager to extract items from one face and insert fuel into a cart from another.
   The external distributer will extend access to the cart manager one block higher when placed on top. This will make using pipes to insert/extract items from the cargo manager easier.

betterquesting.name: Starlight Hookup
betterquesting.desc: Used to connect sources of starlight (such as collector crystals) to other blocks. Right click the source, then right click the block to focus the light on. Remove the wand from your hand to finish the linking process.

betterquesting.name: Hidden Mana Ingot
betterquesting.desc: Unlocks for players who used other methods to make mana infused ingots.

betterquesting.name: Forming the Unusual Alloy
betterquesting.desc: Mana infused ingots can be obtained by drying the molten metal into clumps then pressing them into ingots or by condensing the fluid into nuggets with the fractioning still.

betterquesting.name: Process of Evaporation
betterquesting.desc: Materials needed to build a 4x3x4 evaporation plant. Can be used to create brine and lithium.

betterquesting.name: The Chemist's Research #2
betterquesting.desc: Nature may abhor a vacuum… but this world adores a vacuum tube.  Every variation I try seems to interact with the world around it in a different way.  Some of them light up in my hand the second I create them, others it takes more investigation but all seem to be useful in a variety of ways.  Many of them have proved excellent in the automation of various farms and growth varieties but their most promising use by far has been in automation and logistics, which frees my time for more pressing pursuits

betterquesting.name: The Chemist's Research #1
betterquesting.desc: The wildlife of this world, which seemed at first little more than a painful annoyance (especially the bees), seems to interact with the unrecognizable minerals in exciting ways.  I've tried combining them in different iterations and have already discovered at least two useful byproducts.

betterquesting.name: The Chemist's Research #3
betterquesting.desc: Matter and energy may or may not be interchangeable in this world,  but they are certainly changeable.  Exposing certain minerals to focused laser beams seems to transform them into a more powerful and unpredictable variation and I have begun toying with lenses which cause even more spectacular results!  My newest experiments involve converting various samples of matter into beams of energy that the altered crystal matrices of reconstructed minerals seem to be able to absorb, causing stranger and stranger matter states to coalesce.  They aren't stable yet, but I remain optimistic that with further experimentation I will succeed.

betterquesting.name: The Chemist's Research #4
betterquesting.desc: Now that I have my empowered mineral variants, I can see how truly interconnected the weird physics of this world is. Some sort of mathematic field seems to swirl around them, affecting nearby matter.  I am now experimenting with how these fields interact, exposing items to each other and seeing what strange new form of matter comes out the other side. Some things combine easily, others need more complex mathematics to stabilize the reaction.  For the most dramatic effects, I have found it necessary to add vast amounts of energy into the equation, and the natural electricity formed by the magnetosphere of this planet seems to be the most efficacious of all.  With my conductor mast I am toying with very powerful and dangerous tools indeed.  It's a good thing I shall only use my powers for good! Mostly...

betterquesting.name: Ender Ores
betterquesting.desc: You'll need a cobalt level pick to mine this ore.

betterquesting.name: The Dragon Dimension
betterquesting.desc: If looking for the stronghold triggers your agoraphobia, check out the Random Things artificial end portal multiblock.

betterquesting.name: Material Melter
betterquesting.desc: Hot enough to melt materials down into liquid form.

betterquesting.name: Infusion Upgrade
betterquesting.desc: Powerful infusion crafting boosted by the life force of dragons.

betterquesting.name: Powered Heat
betterquesting.desc: While evaporation can occur with the heat of a biome, the process is much faster when heat is pumped in.

betterquesting.name: Dupe Bugs
betterquesting.desc: The universe now in fear of your great power has reveal the secret of multiplying matter with energy. Requires 1.5 billion RF and 7 circuits.

betterquesting.name: Absorbing the World
betterquesting.desc: Needs 128 blocks for the material absorber or 64 blocks of fluid for the liquid absorber. Check the dimlet workbench for valid dimlet materials.

betterquesting.name: Anti Dragon Cape

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #8
betterquesting.desc: We rule this world as the pharaohs, our powers absolute.  None remain to question us, and none have we found to ask our own questions. Together we shall await the end of the world, or pull destruction up over our heads like blankets when the time comes for sleep...

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #1
betterquesting.desc:
Father or brother? Brother or father?  The question no one is asking, but I can feel it in the air since my own coming of age, especially in the years since my mother drowned in the fires of the nether. It floats in the air, filling overlong silences and catching the light in the corner of your eye, leaving awkward glances behind. I travel a great deal because of it, and no one in this latter age has explored this world as thoroughly as my family.  
   Most of the evidence we find of other stranded Travelers is ephemeral, with little evidence that they managed to travel far or survive for long.  Even in the records left by the most successful of the Travelers, they very rarely find evidence of others and there seems to be only one other clear case of people arriving together as my parents did, though there were three in that group.  How different my life would be if there were just one more person in the wide world!

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #2
betterquesting.desc: None of the journals we have copied, the maps we have marked, the cities we have searched or ravines we have probed have answered any of our questions.  People arrive from… wherever, they survive as best they can, and then they die alone.  I will not let this happen to me.  If there is no hope to be found in this world, I must look beyond it.  Too many have tried to return home from whence they came and failed.  I think I must look the other way and try to pass Beyond.  It seems like some of the unusual alloys and metallics have properties that seem to extend beyond the obvious interaction of this world and touch something else… either of the End, or of the mysterious insides of atom themselves.  I shall experiment and see if any of them opens the doors I need.

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #3
betterquesting.desc: I think sometimes that the easiest door to open would be the one to death… surely I would not be alone there? But the afterlife of this world may be crowded with its own lost souls, all those who built this world before… dying? Leaving? Ascending?  I have performed some experiments to see where the souls of the local inhabitants go when they pass beyond this life.  The answers… do not encourage me to follow them there, tho I continue my experiments and have derived some good from the knowledge.

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #4
betterquesting.desc: There is a more peaceful approach I attempted after becoming embittered by my experiments with the afterlife.  Tho gentler, it was no more successful.  I was ebullient when I first opened what appeared to be a gateway to a new dimension, and a powerful one at that… but all my attempts to pass through have failed.  If there is indeed a world through there, it is not for such life as us.  I have managed to obtain some transformed elements that may help me on my ongoing search for escape.

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #5
betterquesting.desc:
Success! My brother who I long avoided is the one who finally came up with the answer.  I cannot follow the mathematical flights of his intellect but I can fly through the doors he has opened for me… and such doors!  Worlds uncountable, each different and unexpected.  Is our own world just another one of these options that we have been dropped into? Or are we truly creating these worlds each time we pour in a months worth of power and wait to see what we have created?
   And when will one of these worlds be full not just of wonder… but of people?

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #6
betterquesting.desc: Perhaps looking at these endless worlds is fruitless.  What was once so novel is now disheartening.  But there are other hearts to give us courage… dragon hearts.  If we fail as explorers, perhaps we shall succeed as conquerors.  And so we venture further than even we have before.

betterquesting.name: Diamatine Diary #7
betterquesting.desc: I still hear her cries, and the unhatched egg I keep near my as a reminder of our folly and destruction.  Does our own restlessness merit the destruction of such a majestic creature?  In penance, my brother and I fly into the darkest stretches of the End in search of the chaos dragon whose angry roars we hear echoing through the quiet spaces between worlds.  Perhaps he shall guide us home...Or perhaps we shall have to pay the final price for the death of his mate, for we are not the only two creatures who live alone in a world empty of their own kind.
